OL,3,CCouples delaying having children due
OL,4,Cto cost of living, study suggests
OL,6,FIncreases in the cost of living are
OL,7,Fcausing people to put off having
OL,8,Fchildren, with around a fifth of
OL,9,Fcouples saying they'd been forced to
OL,10,Fchange plans due to spiralling prices,
OL,11,Fresearch has suggested.
OL,13,FA survey of more than 4,000 people by
OL,14,Finsurer Royal London found that 22% of
OL,15,Fpeople aged 18 to 34 have made changes
OL,16,Fto family planning because of the
OL,17,Fcrisis.
