OL,6,FMeanwhile, 8% of people in the age
OL,7,Fbracket said they have delayed having
OL,8,Fchildren because they do not have the
OL,9,Fmoney.
OL,11,FThe research found that worsening
OL,12,Feconomic conditions mean the average
OL,13,Ffamily with young children has seen
OL,14,Fexpenses rise by more than #1,000 a
OL,15,Fmonth.
OL,17,FAs a result, 18% of parents questioned
OL,18,Fsaid they have been left with no money
OL,19,Ffor unexpected bills or emergencies.
