OL,6,FConsumer Prices Index (CPI) inflation
OL,7,Fslowed to 2.3% in April, down from
OL,8,F3.2% in March, according to the Office
OL,9,Ffor National Statistics (ONS).
OL,11,FSharp rises in the cost of food,
OL,12,Fenergy and housing in recent years
OL,13,Fhave made the cost of living a central
OL,14,Fissue in the upcoming General Election.
OL,16,FIt comes after similar research by the
OL,17,FResolution Foundation showed that the
OL,18,Fcrisis has changed what households do
OL,19,Fwith their money, with consumption
OL,20,Fbeing cut by more than the fall in
OL,21,Fincomes.
